/* About - Privacy & Disclaimer */
"about.privacy.title" = "Privacy Policy";
"about.disclaimer.title" = "Disclaimer";
"about.privacy.content" = "Glucose Control Assistant Privacy Policy\n\nLast Updated: February 12, 2026\n\n1. Data Collection\nThis app does not collect any personal information to developer servers. All glucose records are stored only on your device locally and in your private iCloud account.\n\n2. Data Storage\n• Local Storage: Glucose records are saved in your device's local database\n• iCloud Sync: If you enable iCloud, data will sync across your devices through your private iCloud account\n• Apple Health: If you authorize, glucose data will sync to the Apple Health app\n\n3. Data Security\n• All local data is protected by iOS system-level encryption\n• iCloud transmission uses TLS encryption\n• Developers cannot access any of your data\n\n4. Third-Party Services\nThis app does not integrate any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs.\n\n5. Data Export & Deletion\n• You can export all data at any time through the settings page (PDF or CSV format)\n• You can delete any record at any time\n• Deleting the app will remove all local data (data in iCloud and Health needs to be managed separately)\n\n6. Contact Us\nFor privacy-related questions, please contact us through the App Store page.";
"about.disclaimer.content" = "Disclaimer\n\nImportant Notice: Please read the following carefully before using this application.\n\n1. Not a Medical Device\nGlucose Control Assistant (XueTangJiLu) is a personal health data recording tool, not a medical device, and does not have medical diagnostic capabilities.\n\n2. No Medical Advice\nThis app does not provide any form of medical diagnosis, treatment advice, or medication guidance. Statistical data shown in the app (such as average glucose, time in range, etc.) are for reference only and should not be used as a basis for medical decisions.\n\n3. Consult Your Doctor\nBefore making any medical decisions, always consult your doctor or professional healthcare provider. Do not adjust medication dosages or treatment plans based solely on data from this app.\n\n4. Data Accuracy\nData recorded in this app is based on user manual input, and data accuracy is the user's responsibility. Please ensure that the glucose values you enter match your glucose meter readings.\n\n5. Emergency Situations\nIf you experience severe hypoglycemia, hyperglycemia, or other medical emergencies, immediately call emergency services or go to the nearest medical facility.\n\n6. Limitation of Liability\nTo the maximum extent permitted by law, the developer is not responsible for any direct or indirect damages arising from the use of this app.";

